{'message': 'For **Battle Ropes**, there are general guidelines for thickness and length to perform the exercise effectively:

- **Thickness**: Typically, battle ropes range from **1.5 to 2 inches in diameter**. Thicker ropes (2 inches) provide more resistance and are better for building strength, while thinner ropes (1.5 inches) allow for faster movements and endurance training.
- **Length**: The standard length is **30 to 50 feet**. Longer ropes create more resistance and wave intensity, while shorter ropes are easier to control for beginners.', 'image_urls': ['https://res.cloudinary.com/dfozfsdqw/image/upload/v1771888912/dzw4uqaqctuj7kae0e9u.jpg']}

